---
import TombstoneLayout from '../layouts/TombstoneLayout.astro';
import { url } from '../lib/url';
---

<TombstoneLayout title="About" description="About the Graveyard of Imaginary Companies project.">
  <article class="max-w-[640px] mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-text mb-8">
      About
    </h1>
    <div class="font-serif text-text space-y-6 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        These companies do not exist. They are generated weekly by an AI and laid to rest here.
        Every Monday, a new tombstone is added. The goal is half satire of startup culture,
        half archaeology of an alternate timeline.
      </p>
      <p>
        None of these companies were funded, sued, acquired, or held a single all-hands.
        They were born and died inside a JSON response.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each entry includes a logo, a landing page that plays it completely straight, and a
        cause of death. The humor, such as it is, comes from the gap between the earnest pitch
        and the inevitable collapse.
      </p>
      <p class="text-muted italic">
        Subscribe via <a href={url('rss.xml')}>RSS</a> to be notified of new deaths.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</TombstoneLayout>
